        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 7 at 3:54PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Basin City to near Burbank. Movement was
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Snake River, Mesa, Connell, and Eltopia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
